   "source": [
    "# Task 1 \u2013 Wildfire Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal:** Transform the raw wildfire CSV into a clean `zip \u00d7 year` table for QML modeling.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Input:** `data/raw/wildfire_data.csv`  \n",
    "**Output:** `data/processed/wildfire_cleaned.csv`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key decisions made in this notebook:**\n",
    "1. The raw file mixes two row types \u2014 fire incidents and weather data \u2014 which we separate first.\n",
    "2. We filter to 2018\u20132023 (train on 2018\u20132022, predict 2023).\n",
    "3. We keep only `OBJECTIVE == 1.0` fires (unplanned, uncontrolled \u2014 per challenge definition).\n",
    "4. We build a complete zip \u00d7 year grid so that zero-fire years are represented.\n",
    "5. Weather NaNs (2022\u20132023 have no weather data) are filled with column medians."
   ]
  },
