   "source": [
    "grid['fire_occurred'] = (grid['fire_count'] > 0).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(grid['fire_occurred'].value_counts())\n",
    "\n",
    "fire_zips = set(fire['zip'].unique())\n",
    "weather_zips = set(grid['zip'].unique())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 \u2013 Add Weather Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Weather rows contain monthly data per ZIP. We aggregate to annual:\n",
    "- `avg_tmax_c` \u2014 average of monthly max temperatures (\u00b0C)\n",
    "- `avg_tmin_c` \u2014 average of monthly min temperatures (\u00b0C)\n",
    "- `tot_prcp_mm` \u2014 total annual precipitation (mm)\n",
    "\n",
    "\u26a0\ufe0f Weather data is only available for 2018\u20132021. Years 2022\u20132023 will be filled with column medians."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(10372, 5)\n",
      "     zip  year  avg_tmax_c  avg_tmin_c  tot_prcp_mm\n",
      "0  90001  2018   22.319292   14.603904        198.1\n",
      "1  90001  2019   21.559567   13.958907        475.7\n",
      "2  90001  2020   22.298544   14.032893        229.6\n",
      "3  90001  2021   20.878253   13.234925        307.3\n",
      "4  90002  2018   22.319292   14.603904        198.1\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "weather_raw = weather_raw.dropna(subset=['zip']).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert types safely\n",
    "weather_raw['zip'] = weather_raw['zip'].astype(int)\n",
    "weather_raw['year'] = weather_raw['year_month'].str[:4].astype(int)\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
